They voted for you, Mr. President, because we told them you’d be on the right side of history when you had to make these calls. Because we knew you’d do the right thing and stop this pipeline.” “Please don’t disappoint us,” the former staffers conclude. “Reject Keystone XL.” On Friday, the 145 former staffers were joined in their opposition by a much more high-profile supporter of the president: Senator Tim Kaine (D-VA).
